
# Valgrind is a powerful tool that can help detect memory mismanagement 
# and leaks. Run your application with Valgrind:
valgrind --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=all --track-origins=yes ./your_application

# The AddressSanitizer (ASan) is another useful tool integrated into 
# GCC and Clang compilers that can detect memory corruption issues:
g++ -fsanitize=address -g your_file.cpp -o your_application

 # Memory corruption error message when application exits: 
 # Generated by the memory management system of the GNU C Library (glibc) on Linux. 
 # Specifically, it comes from the heap memory management subsystem, 
 # which detects inconsistencies or illegal operations on the 
 # heap during memory deallocation.
